\section{Conclusions}

In this paper we further investigated distance properties of convolutional codes over ${\mathbb Z}_{p^r}$ extending the results presented in \cite{no01} for block codes. In particular we have focused our attention on a generalization of the Singleton bound and the class of MDS codes. Continuing the work in \cite{el13} we presented novel results in this direction, \emph{e.g.}, a method to construct MDS for any set of given parameters.

It will be interesting to study these codes equipped with a homogeneous weight \cite{gr00} or different metrics. Another interesting avenue of research is to investigate how we can use these results to construct non-linear (binary) trellis codes.

